* ================================================================
* CONTROLLED SOURCES SPICE MODELS
* VCVS, CCVS, VCCS, CCCS
* ================================================================
* File: controlled_sources.lib
* Description: Library of all four types of controlled sources
* ================================================================

* ================================================================
* 1. VCVS - VOLTAGE-CONTROLLED VOLTAGE SOURCE
* ================================================================
* SPICE Element: E
* Syntax: E<name> N+ N- NC+ NC- <Gain>
*   N+, N-   : Output terminals
*   NC+, NC- : Control (sensing) voltage terminals
*   Gain     : Voltage gain (dimensionless, V/V)
* ================================================================

.SUBCKT VCVS_MODEL NP NM NCP NCM PARAMS: GAIN=1
E_VCVC  NP NM  NCP NCM  {GAIN}
.ENDS VCVS_MODEL


* ================================================================
* 2. CCVS - CURRENT-CONTROLLED VOLTAGE SOURCE
* ================================================================
* SPICE Element: H
* Syntax: H<name> N+ N- V<name> <Transresistance>
*   N+, N-          : Output terminals
*   V<name>         : Name of voltage source for current sensing
*   Transresistance : Transresistance in Ohms (V/A)
* ================================================================

.SUBCKT CCVS_MODEL NP NM SP SM PARAMS: RM=1
V_SENSE  SP SI  DC 0
H_CCVC   NP NM  V_SENSE  {RM}
.ENDS CCVS_MODEL


* ================================================================
* 3. VCCS - VOLTAGE-CONTROLLED CURRENT SOURCE
* ================================================================
* SPICE Element: G
* Syntax: G<name> N+ N- NC+ NC- <Transconductance>
*   N+, N-          : Output current terminals
*   NC+, NC-        : Control (sensing) voltage terminals
*   Transconductance: Transconductance in Siemens (A/V)
* ================================================================

.SUBCKT VCCS_MODEL NP NM NCP NCM PARAMS: GM=1E-3
G_VCCS  NP NM  NCP NCM  {GM}
.ENDS VCCS_MODEL


* ================================================================
* 4. CCCS - CURRENT-CONTROLLED CURRENT SOURCE
* ================================================================
* SPICE Element: F
* Syntax: F<name> N+ N- V<name> <CurrentGain>
*   N+, N-       : Output current terminals
*   V<name>      : Name of voltage source for current sensing
*   CurrentGain  : Current gain (dimensionless, A/A)
* ================================================================

.SUBCKT CCCS_MODEL NP NM SP SM PARAMS: BETA=1
V_SENSE2  SP SI  DC 0
F_CCCS    NP NM  V_SENSE2  {BETA}
.ENDS CCCS_MODEL

